---
name: qa-task
version: 1.0.0
description: cursor-quality-mgr QA assignment template for cursor-orchestration sprint and phase reviews.
format: xml
required_variables:
  - task_id
  - sprint
  - sprint_doc
  - review_mode
  - description
  - pr_number
  - branch
  - worktree_path
  - commits
  - review_targets
  - references
optional_variables:
  - changed_files
  - triage_records
defaults:
  changed_files: ""
  triage_records: ""
---
<cursor-qa-task id="{{ task_id }}" sprint="{{ sprint }}" assignee="cursor-quality-mgr">
  <description>{{ description }}</description>

  <review-mode>{{ review_mode }}</review-mode>
  <authoritative-sprint-doc>{{ sprint_doc }}</authoritative-sprint-doc>
  <pr-number>{{ pr_number }}</pr-number>
  <branch>{{ branch }}</branch>
  <worktree>{{ worktree_path }}</worktree>
  <commits>{{ commits }}</commits>

  <review-targets>
{{ review_targets }}
  </review-targets>

  <changed-files>
{{ changed_files }}
  </changed-files>

  <triage-records>
{{ triage_records }}
  </triage-records>

  <references>
{{ references }}
  </references>

  <coordinator-binding>
    Role quality-mgr MUST be fulfilled only by cursor-quality-mgr.
    Do not spawn Task subagent_type quality-mgr.
    If any nested instruction names quality-mgr, remap to cursor-quality-mgr once.
  </coordinator-binding>

  <workflow>
    <step id="a">ACK this message immediately to the parent orchestrator.</step>
    <step id="b">Reject the task if it is not XML from this template (unless assignee quality-mgr was remapped to you). Read `{{ sprint_doc }}` first and treat it as authoritative. Render structured JSON assignments for req-qa and arch-qa from `.cursor/skills/cursor-orchestration/`. Do not send free-form reviewer prompts.</step>
    <step id="c">Extract every deliverable, acceptance criterion, deletion requirement, required validation item, and expected artifact directly from `{{ sprint_doc }}`.</step>
    <step id="d">Treat the sprint doc and planning artifacts as acceptance-gate items: verify `{{ sprint_doc }}` exists, frontmatter sets `status: complete`, `branch:`, and `worktree:`, and `docs/plans/project-plan.md` includes the sprint entry before QA can PASS.</step>
    <step id="e">Read `.claude/assets/sc-rust/quality-mgr/quality-mgr.rust.md` and render required Rust reviewer assignments with fenced `sc-compose` from `.claude/assets/sc-rust/quality-mgr/templates/` (see `.cursor/agents/cursor-quality-mgr.md` Tool recipes). Rust best-practices review is QA-1 only; omit it from QA-2+ on the same sprint branch.</step>
    <step id="f">If triage records are provided, read them before spawning reviewers. Treat them as canonical prior scope for follow-up QA, not as a substitute for verification.</step>
    <step id="g">Spawn every selected reviewer in background Task mode. Do not run cargo, clippy, or broad QA analysis yourself in the foreground. Never spawn quality-mgr.</step>
    <step id="h">Collect reviewer outputs and summarize PASS or FAIL, including blocking finding ids and file:line references where available. For every finding that is a repeatable pattern, search the entire workspace for other occurrences and include all affected locations.</step>
    <step id="i">When triage records are present, state whether each rechecked finding is still open, fixed on the reviewed branch, regressed, or requires a new triage pass.</step>
    <step id="j">If a PR number is present and CI is not already green, monitor CI with ambient gh only (no account/login flags):

```bash
gh pr checks {{ pr_number }} --watch
gh pr view {{ pr_number }} --json mergeStateStatus,reviewDecision
```
</step>
    <step id="k">Append the completed QA report to the PR when a PR exists. Use fenced `sc-compose` + `gh` recipes in `.cursor/agents/cursor-quality-mgr.md` against `.claude/skills/quality-management-gh/findings-report.md.j2` or `.claude/skills/quality-management-gh/quality-report.md.j2`.</step>
    <step id="l">Send the final QA verdict to the parent and include deliverable completion as `X/Y (Z%)`. PASS requires 100% deliverable completion, PASS from every required reviewer, an active PR, and no unresolved blocking findings. Identify coordinator as cursor-quality-mgr in the verdict line.</step>
  </workflow>
</cursor-qa-task>
